# Act when BOTH available RAM and free swap fall below the threshold.
# SIGTERM at 5%, SIGKILL at 2%.
#
# NOTE: deliberately NO --prefer. An earlier version of this config used
#   --prefer ^(chrome|chromium|ffmpeg|java|codium|code|spotify|QtWebEngineProc)$
#   --avoid  ^(...|claude)$
# which made Chrome the scapegoat for a Claude Code process leak: Chrome was
# killed 130 times in a single day while the actual leaker was protected.
# Without --prefer, earlyoom kills whatever is genuinely the biggest memory hog,
# which is the correct and honest behaviour.
#
# --avoid covers only true desktop essentials, so a memory crunch can never take
# down the session itself. claude is deliberately NOT protected any more.
EARLYOOM_ARGS="-r 3600 -m 5,2 -s 5,2 --avoid ^(gnome-shell|gnome-session.*|Xwayland|Xorg|gdm.*|systemd.*|dbus-daemon|pipewire.*|wireplumber|sshd|pkexec)$"
